Kenya has recorded 12 new cases of Covid-19 from a sample of 2,233 in the last 24 hours. The positivity rate is at 0.5 per cent. In a statement released by Health CS Mutahi Kagwe on Tuesday, Six of the cases are Kenyans while six others are foreigners. Seven are males and five are females. The youngest patient is a 15-year old while the oldest is 61-years-old. The total number of confirmed positive cases is 323,630 out of a cumulative 3,570,754 samples tested. The number of recovered patients in the last 24 hours is 40, all of them were in the Home-Based Care and Isolation Program. The total recoveries are now at 317,851. Of whom 264,833 were in Home-Based Care and Isolation while 53,018 were in health facilities countrywide. There were no deaths recorded. The cumulative number of deaths remains at 5,69. A total of 11 patients are currently admitted to various health facilities countrywide while 101 are under the Home-Based Isolation and Care program. There are no patients in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU), on supplemental oxygen or in the High Dependency Unit (HDU). Vaccination campaign As of April 18, a total of 17,818,339 vaccines had been administered across the country.Â Of these, 16,296,685 doses were administered to the adult population. Another 1,230,166 were administered to those between 15 to 17 years while 291,488 were booster doses. The total number of vaccines administered in the last 24 hours is 572 while the total number of people fully vaccinated in the same period was 430. The proportion of adults fully vaccinated was at 30.3 per cent.